<Layouts.app flash={@flash}>
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 mt-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <.custom_nav active="chelekom-docs-drawer" />
    <div class="lg:col-span-10">
      <.custom_info
        title="Drawer"
        description="Flexible sliding drawers for Phoenix and LiveView with customizable positioning, styling, and interactive show and hide functionality."
        mix="mix mishka.ui.gen.component drawer"
        github="https://github.com/mishka-group/mishka_chelekom/blob/master/priv/components/drawer.eex"
        tags={["Component", "Stateless", "JS-module"]}
      />
      <.custom_tab id="chelekom-drawer-tab">
        <:documentation_panel>
          <.heading2 class="mb-5" id="overview">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/drawer/#overview"}>
              Overview of the Phoenix and LiveView Drawer Component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <strong>
              Mishka Chelekom Drawer
            </strong>
            component allows you to create flexible and customizable sliding panels for displaying hidden content, such as navigation, sidebars, or additional information. It's a versatile component that can be positioned on the left, right, top, or bottom of the viewport, providing an intuitive and accessible way to display or hide content as needed. The drawer can be easily integrated with
            <strong>Phoenix</strong>
            and <strong>Phoenix LiveView</strong>, making it an ideal solution for enhancing user interactivity.
          </.cp>

          <.cp class="mt-5">
            This
            <strong>
              <.link
                title="Phoenix LiveView component"
                class="transition-colors hover:text-[#448D96]"
                navigate={~p"/chelekom"}
              >
                Phoenix LiveView component
              </.link>
            </strong>
            is perfect for enhancing user experience by providing dynamic and interactive sliding panels that can be triggered by various actions, offering both visual appeal and functional utility.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_block position="left" color="success" class="my-8" border="medium">
            <.cp>
              By using the class prop, you can apply custom classes or Tailwind CSS classes to customize the appearance and behavior of the components, allowing for flexible design changes.
            </.cp>
            <strong>Note:</strong>
            id prop is required and each drawer should have unique id.
          </.custom_block>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="drawer-js-modules">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/drawer/#drawer-js-modules"}>
              About LiveView JS module commands
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp class="my-8">
            In the drawer component, there are three attributes that allow users to execute custom LiveView JS commands when certain actions like showing or hiding occur. These attributes are:
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>on_hide:</strong>
                This attribute lets the user execute an additional JavaScript command when the drawer is hidden, alongside the default toggle action. For instance, a user might want to push some data to the server or trigger another function when the drawer hides.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>on_show:</strong>
                This attribute allows you to run a custom JavaScript command when the drawer is shown. Users can, for example, send data, log an event, or perform any other action when the drawer is displayed.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>on_hide_away:</strong>
                This attribute allows for the execution of a JavaScript command when the drawer is hidden by clicking outside of it. This could be useful for logging interactions or sending specific data back to the server.
              </li>
            </ul>
            These attributes give developers more control over the interactions with the drawer, allowing for complex actions to be performed using custom JavaScript beyond just the default show/hide behavior.
          </.cp>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="base-drawer">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/drawer/#base-drawer"}>
              Base Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.custom_code_wrapper
            elements_class="flex gap-5 items-center justify-center"
            code_class="text-sm"
            code={@code_15}
          >
            <.button size="small" phx-click={Drawer.show_drawer("drawer-example-900", "bottom")}>
              Open Base
            </.button>

            <.drawer id="drawer-example-900" position="bottom" size="small">
              <.cp class="p-3">
                The Mishka Chelekom Drawer component is a highly customizable and flexible sliding panel for Phoenix LiveView applications. It allows developers to add content in a side or top/bottom drawer, which can be toggled to show or hide based on user interactions. With built-in support for different positions like left, right, top, and bottom, the drawer can fit into a variety of layouts and use cases. It also provides several customization options, including size, color, and styling variants, making it adaptable to different design needs. The drawer integrates seamlessly with Phoenix LiveView, offering interactive functionality through JavaScript actions for showing, hiding, and reacting to events such as clicking outside the drawer. This makes the Mishka Chelekom Drawer component a practical and essential tool for creating smooth, user-friendly navigation and interactive elements in web applications.
              </.cp>
            </.drawer>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="default-variant-drawer">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/drawer/#default-variant-drawer"}>
              Default Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The default style of the
            <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs/drawer"}>Mishka Chelekom drawer</.link>
            applies a solid background and border that change based on user interaction, making it perfect for delivering important notifications. With just a single setting, you can select from a range of color options, ensuring easy customization to match various design styles. Default variant have also white and dark colors which are the same colors in the dark and light mode.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper
            elements_class="flex gap-5 items-center justify-center"
            code_class="text-sm"
            code={@code_2}
          >
            <.button
              size="small"
              variant="outline"
              color="natural"
              phx-click={Drawer.show_drawer("drawer-example-1", "bottom")}
            >
              Open Natural
            </.button>
            <.button
              size="small"
              color="info"
              variant="outline"
              phx-click={Drawer.show_drawer("drawer-example-2", "top")}
            >
              Open info
            </.button>
            <.button
              size="small"
              color="dawn"
              variant="outline"
              phx-click={Drawer.show_drawer("drawer-example-3", "left")}
            >
              Open Dawn
            </.button>
            <.button
              size="small"
              color="misc"
              variant="outline"
              phx-click={Drawer.show_drawer("drawer-example-4", "right")}
            >
              Open misc
            </.button>

            <.drawer
              id="drawer-example-1"
              variant="default"
              color="natural"
              position="bottom"
              size="small"
            >
              <.cp class="p-3">
                The Mishka Chelekom Drawer component is a highly customizable and flexible sliding panel for Phoenix LiveView applications. It allows developers to add content in a side or top/bottom drawer, which can be toggled to show or hide based on user interactions. With built-in support for different positions like left, right, top, and bottom, the drawer can fit into a variety of layouts and use cases. It also provides several customization options, including size, color, and styling variants, making it adaptable to different design needs. The drawer integrates seamlessly with Phoenix LiveView, offering interactive functionality through JavaScript actions for showing, hiding, and reacting to events such as clicking outside the drawer. This makes the Mishka Chelekom Drawer component a practical and essential tool for creating smooth, user-friendly navigation and interactive elements in web applications.
              </.cp>
            </.drawer>
            <.drawer
              id="drawer-example-2"
              position="top"
              variant="default"
              color="info"
              size="small"
            >
              <.cp class="p-3">
                The Mishka Chelekom Drawer component is a highly customizable and flexible sliding panel for Phoenix LiveView applications. It allows developers to add content in a side or top/bottom drawer, which can be toggled to show or hide based on user interactions. With built-in support for different positions like left, right, top, and bottom, the drawer can fit into a variety of layouts and use cases. It also provides several customization options, including size, color, and styling variants, making it adaptable to different design needs. The drawer integrates seamlessly with Phoenix LiveView, offering interactive functionality through JavaScript actions for showing, hiding, and reacting to events such as clicking outside the drawer. This makes the Mishka Chelekom Drawer component a practical and essential tool for creating smooth, user-friendly navigation and interactive elements in web applications.
