          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>size</.custom_inline_code>
            prop allows developers to control the overall size of the drawer component. It offers predefined values such as <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>, which adjust the width or height of the drawer depending on its position. For drawers positioned on the left or right of the screen, the prop adjusts the width, while for drawers positioned at the top or bottom, it controls the height. This flexibility ensures the drawer can fit various design requirements, making it adaptable for different content and use cases.
          </.cp>

