          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="drawer-position-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/drawer/#drawer-position-prop"}>
              Position prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>position</.custom_inline_code>
            prop controls where the drawer will be displayed on the screen. By default, it is set to <.custom_inline_code>left</.custom_inline_code>, which positions the drawer on the left side of the viewport. The other available values are<.custom_inline_code>
            right
          </.custom_inline_code>,<.custom_inline_code>top</.custom_inline_code>, and<.custom_inline_code>
            bottom
          </.custom_inline_code>, which place the drawer on the corresponding sides of the screen. Each of these positions adjusts the drawer's layout and ensures that it takes the appropriate space and orientation based on the selected position. This flexibility allows developers to choose the best placement for the drawer depending on the design and user interaction requirements.
          </.cp>

